# Git: dual remote push

This repo uses two GitHub remotes:

- **`familyos`** — `https://github.com/dking2451/family-os-mvp.git`
- **`origin`** — `https://github.com/dking2451/Big-Daves-News-.git`

## After any commit

When the user asks to **commit and push** (or only **push**), update **both** remotes:

1. Push the current branch to **`familyos`**.
2. Push the same branch to **`origin`**.

Example (replace `main` with the current branch if different):

```bash
git push familyos HEAD
git push origin HEAD
```

Or use the repo helper: `./scripts/push-remotes.sh` from the repository root.

If a push fails (e.g. one remote rejects or branch missing), report the error clearly and do not claim both succeeded.
